            <h2 class="section-title mb-4">Our History</h2>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8">
                    <p>Founded in 1982, LifeCare General Hospital began as a small community clinic with just 20 beds and a dedicated team of 5 physicians. Over the decades, we've grown into a 300-bed state-of-the-art medical facility serving the entire region.</p>
                    <p>Our expansion has been guided by a commitment to meeting our community's evolving healthcare needs. Major milestones include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>1995:</strong> Opened our cardiac care unit</li>
                        <li><strong>2005:</strong> Established the region's first neonatal intensive care unit</li>
                        <li><strong>2015:</strong> Achieved Level I Trauma Center designation</li>
                        <li><strong>2020:</strong> Opened the new Cancer Treatment Center</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Today, we serve over 100,000 patients annually with a team of 500+ medical professionals across 40+ specialties.</p>
                </div>
